-- Insurer Legal & General to start lending direct to businesses
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 06:04AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 17 (Reuters) - UK insurer Legal & General <LGEN.L> said on Thursday that it plans to start lending direct to businesses across Europe.

The company said it had taken a 40 percent equity stake in Pemberton Asset Management, which is launching a new direct lending platform to provide loans and private placements to mid-market companies.